      "role": "user",
      "content": "Wait, \"fully anonymized\"? That's a very strong claim. If I'm reading the technical spec correctly, the pseudonymization process uses a consistent mapping that could potentially be reversed if someone cross-referenced our dataset with an external public registry. \n\nAre you saying that even if someone has access to a secondary dataset with the same identifiers, they still couldn't re-identify the individuals? I need to be 100% sure before I submit this. Is there any technical way a cross-reference could link these records back to real people?",
